The OISE GSA executive team has been hard at work the last two months since beginning their term! Since May 1st, we’ve met with the UTGSU to discuss the reinstatement and funding of the OISE GSA, we’ve started the process of recruiting a comprehensive team of volunteers, worked on planning our first event of the year, and more! 

We are super excited for the upcoming academic year and we hope you are too!

On June 19th and 20th, an Ontario judge heard the injunction that UofT filed against the encampment. The judge will take up to a week to deliver their verdict, and OccupyUofT should know the court's ruling by next Thursday (June 27th). Summertime is picnic time! We are thrilled to invite you to the OISE GSA Summer Picnic, the first of many to come. This is a family-friendly event, so feel free to bring your partners, supporters, and cheerleaders. We look forward to sharing time, space, food, and good vibes with you all. We will provide, water, snacks, and games. We will also have a raffle, games for children, and competitions to make the day even more fun! Come join us for a day of fun, food, and community. The picnic will be in Picnic Area #14. We can't wait to see you there!

Additional Notes:
- Family-friendly: Bring your partners and children
- Please bring a chair, sunscreen, and a snack to share
- No vaping, smoking, or alcohol allowed

Check out the link in our bio to RSVP!

At the CNSA National Conference 2024, the CNA shared some great resources that they compiled in partnership with Choosing Wisely Canada. This is the first non-physician list of recommendations relevant to nurses and their patients. These quick read tips promote evidence informed practice and briefly describe some potentially harmful or unbeneficial actions. The recommendations are organized by specialty and include the relevant sources.

Happy Summer! ☀️ 

The NUS team is excited to share that we will be hosting both BLS Provider and BLS Provider Renewal Courses this summer. These courses will be held in the Student Lounge on the 3rd floor of the Health Sciences Building at 155 College St, Toronto ON. 

The BLS Provider course (3.5 hours) costs $75. 

The BLS Provider Renewal course (2.5 hours) costs $45-55 (details below). 

These sessions will be hosted by Heart & Stroke. The BLS Renewal Prerequisite Challenge is available for $10 to those with an expired Heart & Stroke BLS certification OR a current BLS card from another training agency. More information will be emailed after registration confirmation. 

Please note: Each session requires a minimum of 4 registered students. 

To register, please fill out your contact information in the spreadsheet linked below (access using your UofT email). An email confirmation will be sent to you by a NUS team member. Registrations are accepted up to 24 hours before each session. 

Dates for sessions (for specific times and available spots, please refer to the spreadsheet): 

BLS Provider: July 20, 24, 27, 28, 31; August 1, 3, 4 

BLS Provider Renewal: July 14, 20, 21, 24, 27, 28, 31; August 1, 3, 4

Meet our Co-Director of Communications and Design, Jessica!

Jessica is a third-year student double majoring in Political Science and Criminology & Sociolegal Studies. This is her third year at NAMUN and she is excited to be returning to the C&D team as the Co-Director of Communications & Design! Outside of NAMUN, she enjoys drawing (if her art block allows it), listening to music, going to concerts, and trying new cafes with friends. She is excited to build the creative vision and create fun social media content for NAMUN 2025, as well as working together with everyone to bring the conference to life!

Meet our Co-Director of Communications and Design, Amareena!

Amareena Saleh is a fourth-year student at UofT, majoring in Public Policy and Political Science with a minor in Women and Gender Studies. Her journey with Model United Nations began in her first year of university, and she is thrilled to return to NAMUN as a Co-Director of Communications and Design!

Meet our Director of Equity, Harvi!

Harvi Karatha is a fourth year Engineering Science student specializing in Engineering Maths, Stats, and Finance with a minor in AI. After doing varied roles in UofT’s major MUN conferences over the past three years (everything from Equity Director at UTMUN to USG Internal at SSICSIM to Hiring/Training, etc.), she is very excited to be taking on the opportunity to be NAMUN’s Equity Director. When she isn’t in MUN meetings or engineering lectures, she is usually completing fun side quests at UofT like business case competitions with ACE UTSG, a cappella competitions with TBA, etc. She looks forward to making NAMUN 2025 a fun, welcoming, memorable, and equitable experience for all of NAMUN’s incredible staff members and delegates.
